article.headline: Hofstra 69, James Madison 66
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Loren Stokes had 18 points and 11 rebounds and Wendell Gibson had 18 points and 10 rebounds on Wednesday night as Hofstra held off a late comeback by James Madison to win 69-66. The Dukes trailed by as many as 23 in the second half, but Chris Williams made a layup with 1:27 remaining to cut the deficit to 66-63. But they could not get any closer. The Pride added three free throws in the final 18 seconds and Williams made a 3-pointer for James Madison at the buzzer for the final margin. Kenny Adeleke scored 14 points for the Pride (7-10, 3-4 Colonial Athletic Association), who led at the half 33-20. Carlos Rivera added 10. Daniel Freeman paced the Dukes (4-11, 1-6) with 19 points, 14 in the second half, and Williams finished with 12. David Cooper led James Madison with nine rebounds, but the Dukes were outrebounded 48-29.
